  "prompt": "Where is travencore state in India?",
  "response": "Travancore is a historical princely state located in the southwestern region of India, primarily in the present-day state of Kerala. It was situated along the Malabar Coast, bordered by the Arabian Sea to the west and the Western Ghats to the east. Travancore was an important regional power before India gained independence in 1947. Today, the territory that was once Travancore encompasses several districts in Kerala, including Thiruvananthapuram (the capital city), Kollam, and parts of other adjacent districts.",
